<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Defs>
    
    
    
    <XmlExtensions.SettingsMenuDef>
        <defName>TPatches1FixSomeModdedFactionsNotShowingUpInCreateWorldMenu</defName> <!--Can be anything unique with no periods-->
        <modId>carnap2.TPatches</modId> <!--MUST be the same as the one entered earlier-->    
        <label>TPatches</label> <!-- This is what displays as your mod's name-->    
        <settings> <!--This is where you define what settings are in the settings menu-->
            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.TabView">
                <tabs>
                    <li>
                        <label>Info</label>
                        <settings>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                                <text>Make sure TPatches is loaded as close to the end as possible. It can only affect mods that are loaded before it.</text>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                                <text>All XML Extensions settings require a restart to be applied!</text>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Gap">
                                <spacing>12</spacing>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                                <text>Settings in this mod should have zero performance impact. Settings for mods you don't have are greyed out. You can still use those settings, in case you might install those mods in the future.</text>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                                <text>If you run into problems adding TPatches into an existing save, try disabling Duplicate Animal Remover. DAR completely deletes duplicate animals, meaning they won't be loaded if you happen to have them on the map in your save. With that being said, usually removing animals even when they are on the map shouldn't cause any problems.</text>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine"/>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                                <text>Duplicate Animals Remover log:</text>
                            </li>
                        </settings>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <label>Fixes</label>
                        <settings>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor">
                                <color>(255,255,255)</color>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Gap">
                                <spacing>12</spacing>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Section">
                                <settings>
                                    <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                                        <key>TPatchesDAR</key>
                                        <label>Duplicate Animal Remover</label>
                                        <tooltip>this xpath contains a manually collected list of rules for removing animals when appropriate mods are loaded. Removes ThingDef, PawnKindDef and egg ThingDef. When a higher priority mod is detected, it tries to remove duplicate animals from lower priority mods. You can see the mod priority on TPatches Google Sheets.</tooltip>
                                    </li>
                                    <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                                        <font>Tiny</font>
                                        <text>This will remove duplicate animals from mods. Vanilla Expanded mods are the highest priority and animals from them won't be removed. For example, if both VE and ACP add a Cheetah, it will be deleted from ACP. Some animals are renamed instead where appropriate.</text>
                                    </li>
                                </settings>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Gap">
                                <spacing>12</spacing>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Section">
                                <settings>
                                    <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                                        <key>TPatchesTypoCorrecter</key>
                                        <label>Typo Correcter</label>
                                        <tooltip>this xpath contains a manually collected list of rules for replacing texts with corrected versions.</tooltip>
                                    </li>
                                    <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                                        <font>Tiny</font>
                                        <text>Corrects text typos in mods. For example, renames "crocodale" to "crocodile", "leopardgecko" to "leopard gecko", etc. Currently does a complete retranslation of HC_Animal_1, HC_Animal_2, HC_Animal_3, HC_Animal_4.</text>
                                    </li>
                                </settings>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Gap">
                                <spacing>12</spacing>
                            </li>
                            <!-- following defs are replaced by patches -->
                            <carnap2TPatches1></carnap2TPatches1> <!-- factions fixer -->
                            <!--As many settings in this tab as you want-->
                        </settings>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <label>Settings</label>
                        <settings>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor">
                                <color>(255,255,255)</color>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                                <text>Nothing here yet...</text>
                            </li>
                        </settings>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <label>Specific tweaks</label>
                        <settings>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor">
                                <color>(255,255,255)</color>
                            </li>
                            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Gap">
                                <spacing>12</spacing>
                            </li>
                            <carnap2TPatches2></carnap2TPatches2> <!-- specific HAR fixes -->
                        </settings>
                    </li>
                    <!--As many tabs as you want-->
                </tabs>
            </li>
        </settings>
    </XmlExtensions.SettingsMenuDef>
    
    
</Defs>
